{
  "texts": [
    "Again, these systems will require rigorous validation, transparent regulation, and clarity on workforce implications.",
    "In underserved and unserved service areas, AI-supported care delivery may bridge gaps, offering continued access outside of traditional in-person sessions.",
    "AI can generate intervention materials (Pierce, 2024a), and speech analysis algorithms have accurately classified correct sound production in children for 80% of phonemes (Carl et al., 2024; Saz et al., 2009).",
    "Such applications will save time, and effort on part of SLPs.",
    "It could allow children to practice speech sounds at home without requiring constant supervision from an SLP."
  ]
}